#1 LoginPage information

Summary:
Verify LoginPage information

STR
1. Open loginPage via URL https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/

EX
The following information should be presented:
1. Username input in Sign in section
2. Password input in Sign in section
3. Sign In button
4. Username input in Sign Up section
5. Email input in Sign Up section
6. Password input in Sign Up section
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#2 Sign Up functionality
Summary:
A User should be able to create account using Sign Up function

STR
1. Open loginPage via URL https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/
2. Enter unique Username into Username input in Sign up section  using latin letters (example: )
3. Enter valid email (example: example@emai.com)into Email input in Sign up section
4. Enter Password using latin letters and numbers into Password input in Sign up section. Password should be at least 12 characters

5. Click on 'Sign up for OurApp' button
EX_1
HomePage should appear. The following information should display:
1. Username in right top corner
2. 'Create Post' button available
3. 'Sign Out' button available
4. Search icon available
5. Chat icon available
6. My Profile icon is available

STR continue
6. Click on Sign Out on the top right corner

EX_2
LoginPage displayed
2. 'Create Post' button is not  available
3. 'Sign Out' button is not available
4. Search icon is not available
5. Chat icon is not available
6. 'Sign In' button available
7. My Profile icon is not available

STR continue
7. Enter User name (Created in step 2) into Username input in Sign In section
8. Enter password (Created in step 4) into Password input in Sign In section
9. Hit 'Sign In' button

EX_3
HomePage should appear. The following information should display:
1. Correct Username appears in right top corner
2. 'Create Post' button is available
3. 'Sign Out' button is available
4. Search icon is available
5. Chat icon is available
6. My Profile icon is available
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#3 Verify 'Create Post' Page information
Summary:
'Create Post' Page should be available for users, where they will be able to create posts

Pre-condition:
Login to an existing account using valid data (Username: Myntyan, Password: MuntyanMuntyan).
If the user is not available, register a new user.
HomePage should be open

STR:
1. HomePage should be open https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/
2. Click on 'Create Post' button

EX
1. Create-post page is open.
2. Title input should be available
3. Body Content input should be available
4. Checkbox 'Is this post unique?' should be available
5. 'Select value' Drop Down should be available with 3 options:
    5.1. 'Загальнодоступне'
    5.2. 'Приватне повідомлення'
    5.3. 'Групове повідомлення'
6. 'Create Post' button is available
7. 'Sign Out' button is available
8. Search icon is available
9. Chat icon is available
10. My Profile icon is available
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#4  Create Post function

Summary:
User should be able to Create Post

Pre-condition:
Login to an existing account using valid data (Username: Myntyan, Password: MuntyanMuntyan).
If the user is not available, register a new user.
HomePage should be open

STR:
1. HomePage should be open https://qa-complexapp.onrender.com/
2. Click on 'Create Post' button
3. Enter the following text into Title input: 'Java Stands For'
4. Enter the following text into Body Content input: 'Java doesn't have any abbreviations. Java is rich aromatic coffee seed'
5. Hit 'Save New Post' button

EX_1:
1. Title input should not be available
2. Body Content input should not be available
3. Checkbox 'Is this post unique?' should not be available
4. 'Select value' Drop Down should not be available
6. 'Create Post' button is available
7. 'Sign Out' button is available
8. Search icon available
9. Chat icon available
10. Message 'New post successfully created.' is displayed
11. Delete button available
12.  Edit button is available
13. Profile Link should be available

STR continue:
6. Click on 'My Profile' button

EX_2:
1. 'Java stands For' button appear

STR continue:
7. Click on 'Java stands For' button

EX_3:
1. Delete button available
2.  Edit button is available
3. Sign 'Java Stands For' is displayed
4. Sign 'Java doesn't have any abbreviations. Java is rich aromatic coffee seed' is displayed

